'''Toms'''（又作'''TOMS'''）是一家[[企業|營利性質]]公司，<ref name="Fairfield Citizen - For/Non Profit">{{en}}{{cite news|last=Walkley|first=Alison|title=TOMS founder Mycoskie comes to SHU|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=FFCB&p_theme=ffcb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=12C1F93A276A9768&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|accessdate=12 July 2012|newspaper=Fairfield Citizen|date=2009-11-20|archive-date=2014-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140218214556/http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=FFCB&p_theme=ffcb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=12C1F93A276A9768&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="For-Profit Status">{{en}}{{cite web|title=For Profit or Non-Profit?: Is Toms a non-profit organization?|url=http://www.toms.com/faq/|publisher=Toms Shoes|accessdate=19 December 2010|archive-date=2015-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228044733/http://www.toms.com/faq|dead-url=no}}</ref>總部設於[[加利福尼亞州|加利福尼亞州]][[聖莫尼卡|聖莫尼卡]]，Friends of Toms則為他們經營的非營利子公司。由一位來自[[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]][[阿靈頓_(德克薩斯州)|阿靈頓]]的企業家{{link-en|布雷克·麥考斯基|Blake Mycoskie}}在2006年成立。<ref>{{en}}{{cite news| title = A Mile in his Shoes| work = Fort Worth, Texas: The City's Magazine| publisher = Fort Worth Texas Magazine| last = Blair| first = Jennifer| page = 38| date = January 2009}}</ref><ref name="CNN2">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/BUSINESS/09/26/mycoskie.profile/|work=CNN.com|title=Blake Mycoskie: Sole ambition|last=Wong|first=Grace|date=September 26, 2008|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2009-04-08|archive-date=2009-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090429193518/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/BUSINESS/09/26/mycoskie.profile/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="fortune">{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://postcards.blogs.fortune.cnn.com/2008/10/11/power-point-be-the-change/|title=Power Point: Be the change|work=Fortune|last=Sellers|first=Patricia|date=October 11, 2008|publisher=[[Cable_News_Network|Cable News Network]]|accessdate=2009-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090429204104/http://postcards.blogs.fortune.cnn.com/2008/10/11/power-point-be-the-change/|archive-date=2009-04-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>公司根據阿根廷的{{link-en|麻底帆布鞋|Espadrille}}來設計與銷售鞋子，他們也設計眼鏡。<ref name="CNN">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2009/LIVING/homestyle/03/26/blake.mycoskie.toms.shoes/|title=These shoes help others get a step up|last=Cook|first=Shannon|date=March 26, 2009|work=CNN.com|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2009-04-08|archive-date=2009-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090331140326/http://www.cnn.com/2009/LIVING/homestyle/03/26/blake.mycoskie.toms.shoes/|dead-url=no}}</ref>當Toms賣出一雙鞋時，將會給予一位貧困的孩童一雙鞋；當Toms賣出一對眼鏡時，一部分的利潤將會用於保護與恢復開發中國家人民的視力。
==公司歷史==
布雷克·麥考斯基在2002年與他的妹妹參加《[[驚險大挑戰|驚險大挑戰]]》的[[驚險大挑戰2|第二季]]，初次造訪阿根廷。他在2006年1月再次返回那裡度假，而他在那注意到當地的馬球選手都穿著一種名為alpargatas的鞋子；一種方便穿脫的帆布鞋，之後麥考斯基也開始穿上這款鞋子。阿根廷的農夫數百年來也穿著這款鞋，在這之後也成了Toms鞋的經典款。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/blake-mycoskie |title=Blake Mycoskie |publisher=Huffington Post |accessdate=February 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-05-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505152355/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/blake-mycoskie/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>它們是由帆布和棉織品製成的，而現在還有著許多不同的式樣，像是Cordones系列、Botas系列、Wedges系列、Stitchouts系列和Wrap Boots系列。而這些鞋底都是由橡膠製成的。<ref name="CNN"/>麥考斯基在之後一次的旅途中，來到了[[布宜諾斯艾利斯|布宜諾斯艾利斯]]的郊區當志工，他注意到當地許多孩子都是赤腳在街上奔跑。之後他發現缺乏鞋子的問題不僅是在這個社區而已，而是整個阿根廷甚至是其他開發中的國家，他便決定研製一種alpargata鞋以銷售到北美市場，並且保證當賣出一雙鞋時，他將會無條件提供給阿根廷和其他開發中國家的赤腳青年一雙全新的鞋。<ref name=DFEI />麥考斯基瞭解到鞋子的缺乏對這些青年來說有著嚴重的影響，將會危害到孩子們上學、預防傳染病等的能力。<ref name=Boone>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=THK6--UDyiIC&pg=PA138&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |pages=137–138 |title=Contemporary Business |author=Louis E. Boone and David L. Kurtz |publisher=Wiley & Sons |year=2011 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508042912/http://books.google.ca/books?id=THK6--UDyiIC&pg=PA138&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>

他將想法建立在製造阿根廷鞋，並在這之後成立了公司，最剛開始製造了250雙鞋。公司在2006年5月開始正式銷售他們的鞋款。<ref name=DFEI />在《[[洛杉磯時報|洛杉磯時報]]》刊登出一篇報導後，公司接到了9次的庫存訂單，<ref name=DFEI />並且在頭6個月賣出了10,000雙鞋。首批的免費鞋子在2006年10月分發給阿根廷的孩童，數量相當於當時銷售的庫存量：一萬雙。<ref name="CNN2"/><ref>{{en}}{{cite book |pages=188–89 |title=Buzz: Real Life Lessons in Word-of-Mouth Marketing |author=Emanuel Rosen |publisher=Profile Books |year=2010 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=JxGZTajx9VAC&pg=PA191&dq=history+of+TOMS+shoes&hl=en&sa=X&ei=TxicULugJuS22gW2sIHYCg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |archive-date=2014-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508025645/http://books.google.ca/books?id=JxGZTajx9VAC&pg=PA191&dq=history+of+TOMS+shoes&hl=en&sa=X&ei=TxicULugJuS22gW2sIHYCg&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Seattle">{{en}}{{cite news| title = Happy feet: Buy a pair of Toms shoes and a pair will be donated to a poor child abroad| work = seattlepi.com| publisher = Hearst Seattle Media, LLC| last = Chansanchai| first = Athima| date = June 11, 2007| url = http://www.seattlepi.com/lifestyle/319343_tomsshoes12.html| accessdate = 2009-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{en}}{{cite news| title = For-profit helps keep charity running| work = Marketplace| publisher = American Public Media| last = Brune| first = Brett| date = December 28, 2007| url = http://marketplace.publicradio.org/display/web/2007/12/28/toms_shoes/| accessdate = 2009-04-08| deadurl = yes| archiveurl = https://archive.is/20071220004451/http://marketplace.publicradio.org/display/web/2007/12/28/toms_shoes/| archivedate = 2007-12-20}}</ref>公司當時是自負盈虧的，使得麥考斯基以50萬美金賣掉了他的線上[[駕訓班|駕訓班]]公司，<ref name=DFEI>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://danielsethics.mgt.unm.edu/pdf/TOMS%20Case.pdf |title=TOMS: One for One Movement |author=Alicja Spaulding, Stephanie Fernandez, and Jennifer Sawayda |publisher=Daniels Fund Ethics Initiative at the [[University_of_New_Mexico|University of New Mexico]] |year=2011 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2012-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120617012711/http://danielsethics.mgt.unm.edu/pdf/TOMS%20Case.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>以提供鞋子公司資金。公司的名稱（TOMS）是取自於英文單字“tomorrow”，<ref name="CNN"/>並且從最初的概念演變為“Shoes for Tomorrow Project”。<ref name="OK">{{cite news|url=http://newsok.com/shoes-offer-a-better-tomorrow/article/3358735|work=NewsOK|title=Shoes offer a better tomorrow|last=Miller|first=Linda|date=April 5, 2009|publisher=NewsOK.com|accessdate=2009-04-08|archive-date=2009-04-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090429234819/http://newsok.com/shoes-offer-a-better-tomorrow/article/3358735|dead-url=no}}</ref>

公司在2007年推出了一年一度的「一日不穿鞋」<ref group="註">原文：One Day Without Shoes</ref>活動，追隨者將在一天當中完全不穿鞋，以增加Toms對衣物困乏孩童的認識。現今已經有像是[[美國線上|美國線上]]、[[Flickr|Flickr]]和[[探索頻道|探索頻道]]這些合作夥伴來幫助推動這項活動。到了2011年，全球已經有超過500家零售商在銷售這個品牌；這年它也推出了自有的眼鏡系列。到了2012年，更是已經將超過200萬雙鞋送給了全球各地發展中國家的孩子。[[新墨西哥大學|新墨西哥大學]]的丹尼爾斯基金道德倡議（The Daniels Fund Ethics Initiative）描述這家公司為「一家有慈善成分的營利企業」<ref group="註">原文：a for-profit business with a philanthropic component</ref>。<ref name=DFEI /><ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.onedaywithoutshoes.com |title=What is One Day Without Shoes? |publisher=onedaywithoutshoes.com |date= |accessdate=February 8, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111193942/http://www.onedaywithoutshoes.com/ |archive-date=2019-01-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=B9diOWV8X_UC&pg=PA54&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |page=54 |title=Business & Society: Ethics & Stakeholder Management |author=Archie B. Carroll, Ann K. Buchholtz |year=2008 |publisher=Cengage |access-date=2014-05-07 |archive-date=2014-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508043057/http://books.google.ca/books?id=B9diOWV8X_UC&pg=PA54&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{en}}{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/10/toms-one-day-without-shoes_n_1414470.html |date=April 10, 2012 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |title=TOMS Shoes Annual 'One Day Without Shoes,' Plus Barefoot Celebs |publisher=''[[Huffington_Post|Huffington Post]]'' |author=Julee Wilson |archive-date=2014-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508042856/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/04/10/toms-one-day-without-shoes_n_1414470.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==商業模式==
==="One for One"===
Toms的商業模式已經被稱作為「一對一概念」<ref group="註">原文：one for one concept</ref>的商業模式，指的是公司承諾每賣出一項產品時，將會提供一雙免費的鞋子、全新的鞋子給需要的孩童。曾收到這些免費產品的國家包括阿根廷、衣索比亞、瓜地馬拉、海地、盧旺達、南非以及美國。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=MVrpHJu59M8C&pg=PA57&dq=TOMS+shoes+one+for+one&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Nz-cUPSCJ8il2AWWsIE4&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20one%20for%20one&f=false |page=57 |title=We First: How Brands and Consumers Use Social Media to Build a Better World |author=Simon Mainwaring |year=2011 |publisher=Macmillan |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222052126/http://books.google.ca/books?id=MVrpHJu59M8C&pg=PA57&dq=TOMS+shoes+one+for+one&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Nz-cUPSCJ8il2AWWsIE4&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20one%20for%20one&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>而他們的生產線也不僅局限於鞋類，同時還有眼鏡和服飾。公司靠著顧客間口耳相傳來達到宣傳產品的效果，同時他們依然專注於企業的社會責任。「Friends of Toms」是最初這個雛形的一部份，用來招募自願者到國外幫忙發送這些鞋子。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=2yGWTM_kxegC&pg=PT575&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |author=Jay Kandampully |title=Service Management |year=2012 |publisher=Springer |access-date=2014-05-08 |archive-date=2014-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221045058/http://books.google.ca/books?id=2yGWTM_kxegC&pg=PT575&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>Toms便以「One for One」登記為他們的商標，來形容他們自己的商業模式。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=OpAkaDLAAy4C&pg=PA87&dq=TOMS+eyewear&hl=en&sa=X&ei=6lacUNXCAuOh2QWFh4GQDg&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q&f=false |page=87 |title=Good Works!: Marketing and Corporate Initiatives that Build a Better World...and the Bottom Line |year=2012 |author=Philip Kotler, David Hessekiel, and Nancy Lee |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222181507/http://books.google.ca/books?id=OpAkaDLAAy4C&pg=PA87&dq=TOMS+eyewear&hl=en&sa=X&ei=6lacUNXCAuOh2QWFh4GQDg&ved=0CD0Q6AEwAg#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===專注於企業責任===
作家{{link-en|丹尼爾·H·平克|Daniel H. Pink}}形容這家公司的商業模式為「明確地建立最大化的目標」<ref group="註">原文：expressly built for purpose maximization</ref>，即Toms既賣鞋也賣他們的理想；能產生來購買鞋的消費者，並且透過這個消費行為將他們轉變為捐助者——若這不是消費者的目的，則公司將會幫他們達成這個目的。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=A-agLi2ldB4C&pg=PA134&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |page=134 |title=Drive: The Surprising Truth about what Motivates Us |author={{link-en|丹尼爾·H·平克|Daniel H. Pink|Daniel H. Pink}} |publisher=Penguin |year=2011 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2013-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207132544/http://books.google.ca/books?id=A-agLi2ldB4C&pg=PA134&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>另外還有一個短語「caring capitalism」（有愛的資本主義）用來描述這個獨一無二的商業模式。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=wbAmkdoG4O8C&pg=PA148&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Introduction to Management |year=2010 |author=John R. Schermerhorn |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |page=148 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006121438/http://books.google.ca/books?id=wbAmkdoG4O8C&pg=PA148&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qUGcUIOECYTC2QXCyYDYDA&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>公司在產品轉成收入前，先將捐獻納入他們的商業模式，並使這個行為成為他們不可或缺的創造收入方面的商業模式，以此作為他們發展這句短語的一部份。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=Df4IXyDnYwMC&pg=PA118&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=8FKcUPbHFeWg2AXh3YGICw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |page=118 |title=Values-Centered Entrepreneurs and Their Companies |year=2010 |author=David Y. Choi, Edmund Gray, and Edmund R. Gray |publisher=Taylor & Francis |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006085604/http://books.google.ca/books?id=Df4IXyDnYwMC&pg=PA118&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=8FKcUPbHFeWg2AXh3YGICw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=TOMS%20shoes%20business%20model&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>身為[[維珍集團|維珍集團]]創辦人的商業大亨[[李察·布蘭遜|李察·布蘭遜]]在他的著作《Screw Business as Usual》中寫道這家公司的商業模式，他說「他們根據經濟、健康和教育需求方面，尋求能夠透過TOMS獲得最大受益的社群，同時也顧及到當地的企業，以免產生一種相互關聯的負面影響。」<ref group="註">原文："They look for communities that will benefit most from TOMS based on their economic, health and education needs while taking into account local business so as not to create a correlating negative effect."</ref>他同時也談到關於Toms進軍眼鏡市場，是為了發展中國家將近300萬的視覺受損人士。<ref>{{en}}{{cite book |url=http://books.google.ca/books?id=ABGxCLAaxl8C&pg=PT217&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=8FKcUPbHFeWg2AXh3YGICw&redir_esc=y |title=Screw Business As Usual |author=Richard Branson |publisher=Penguin |year=2011 |page=ebook |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |archive-date=2014-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006224945/http://books.google.ca/books?id=ABGxCLAaxl8C&pg=PT217&dq=TOMS+shoes+business+model&hl=en&sa=X&ei=8FKcUPbHFeWg2AXh3YGICw&redir_esc=y |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==慈善事業==
===合夥===
Toms在2009年以非洲拓展計劃（Africa Outreach Project）與[[莎莉·賽隆|莎莉·賽隆]]合作創造限量版鞋款，盈利將用於非洲偏遠地區的教育與愛滋病患的醫療支援。<ref>{{en}}{{cite news |url=http://www.wwd.com/footwear-news/business/charlize-theron-designs-for-toms-shoes-2398200 |date=December 18, 2009 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |title=Charlize Theron Designs for Toms Shoes |author=JOCELYN ANDERSON |publisher=''Women's Wear Daily'' |archive-date=2014-02-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219182755/http://www.wwd.com/footwear-news/business/charlize-theron-designs-for-toms-shoes-2398200 |dead-url=no }}</ref>Toms也曾以翹八字鬍標記取代傳統的Toms標誌來生產鞋子，以支持[[Movember|Movember基金會]]。<ref>{{en}}{{cite news |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/alltherage/2011/10/toms-shoes-x-movember.html?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+alltherageblog+%28All+The+Rage+Blog%29&utm_content=Google+International |publisher=''[[洛杉磯時報|Los Angeles Times]]'' |title=Toms Shoes X Movember: Some panache with that 'stache? |date=October 18, 2011 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |author=Adam Tschorn |archive-date=2014-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140506070044/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/alltherage/2011/10/toms-shoes-x-movember.html?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+alltherageblog+%28All+The+Rage+Blog%29&utm_content=Google+International |dead-url=no }}</ref>Toms同時也與慈善機構{{link-en|水慈善|charity: water}}合作許多年，像是WaterForward計畫，旨在透過代表他們的朋友將乾淨的水源帶給未開發的國家。<ref>{{en}}{{cite news |url=http://www.fastcompany.com/1790136/trickle-forward-economics-scott-harrisons-water-based-experiment-viral-philanthropy |publisher=''[[Fast_Company_(magazine)|Fast Company]]'' |author=GREGORY FERENSTEIN |date=October 24, 2011 |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |title=Trickle-Forward Economics: Scott Harrison's Water-Based Experiment In Viral Philanthropy |archive-date=2014-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411015300/http://www.fastcompany.com/1790136/trickle-forward-economics-scott-harrisons-water-based-experiment-viral-philanthropy |dead-url=no }}</ref>另外一個合作慈善夥伴是FEED，當消費者買下一雙鞋時，公司除了給一位貧窮孩童一雙鞋外，還會捐贈12餐給貧困的學校。<ref>{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.feedprojects.com/shopping_product_detail.asp?pid=49866&catID=3675 |title=FEED 12 Toms Shoes |accessdate=November 8, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120418052621/http://www.feedprojects.com/shopping_product_detail.asp?pid=49866&catID=3675 |archivedate=2012年4月18日 }}</ref>

==反應==
===對「Buy One, Give One」模式的批評===
Toms受到{{link-en|國際發展|International Development}}組織的批評。<ref name= "Slate: Is TOMS Shoes Listening to its Critics?">{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_world_/2013/10/17/toms_shoes_to_begin_producing_shoes_in_haiti_will_this_be_a_more_effective.html|title=TOMS shoes to begin producing shoes in Haiti. Will this be a more effective way to help the poor?|publisher=slate.com|accessdate=2014-01-25|archive-date=2013-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131221022744/http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_world_/2013/10/17/toms_shoes_to_begin_producing_shoes_in_haiti_will_this_be_a_more_effective.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Come To Africa For Business, Not Handouts">{{en}}{{cite web |url=http://www.peacecorpsconnect.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ComeToAfricaForBusinessNotHandouts_WV.pdf |format=PDF |title=Come To Africa For Business, Not Handouts |last=Buckler |first=Michael |last2=Jackson |first2=Beau |work=peacecorpsconnect.org |publisher=National Peace Corps Association |date=2013 |accessdate=2014-05-08 |archive-date=2013-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217044106/http://www.peacecorpsconnect.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ComeToAfricaForBusinessNotHandouts_WV.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref>他們表示Toms模式旨在使消費者感覺良好，並不能解決潛在的貧窮。<ref name="fastcoexist">{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://www.fastcoexist.com/1679628/the-broken-buy-one-give-one-model-three-ways-to-save-toms-shoes|title=The Broken "Buy-One, Give-One" Model: 3 Ways To Save Toms Shoes | Co.Exist | ideas + impact|publisher=fastcoexist.com|accessdate=2014-01-25|archive-date=2014-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140210150436/http://www.fastcoexist.com/1679628/the-broken-buy-one-give-one-model-three-ways-to-save-toms-shoes|dead-url=no}}</ref>同時也有批評指向捐贈鞋子是否能如其他慈善機構的捐款一樣有效。<ref name="foreignpolicy">{{cite web|url=http://www.foreignpolicy.com/articles/2011/10/11/haiti_doesnt_need_your_old_tshirt?page=full|title=Haiti Doesn't Need Your Old T-Shirt|publisher=foreignpolicy.com|accessdate=2014-01-25|archive-date=2014-01-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102230013/http://www.foreignpolicy.com/articles/2011/10/11/haiti_doesnt_need_your_old_tshirt?page=full|dead-url=no}}</ref>Toms的創辦人{{link-en|布雷克·麥考斯基|Blake Mycoskie}}在2013年11月回應了這些批評，他說「如果你真的要認真看待緩和貧困，或者就如批評家所說，那麼你就需要創造就業機會。起初我把這些批評看作對我個人的謾罵，但後來我意識到這些評論是對的……我們接下來的目標就是用我們的商業模式來創造就業機會。」<ref group="註">原文："If you really are serious about poverty alleviation, our critics said, then you need to create jobs. At first I took that personally, but then I realized that they were right... using our model to create jobs is the next level."</ref><ref name="Toms CEO Blake Mycoskie Offers Surprising Answer To His Critics">{{en}}{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/11/14/toms-ceo-critics_n_4274637.html|title=Toms CEO Blake Mycoskie Offers Surprising Answer To His Critics|publisher=huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=2014-01-25|first=Kevin|last=Short|date=November 14, 2013|archive-date=2013-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220184357/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/11/14/toms-ceo-critics_n_4274637.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>公司宣布他們計畫在2015年将三分之一的鞋由得到送鞋援助的國家生產製造。<ref name="toms">{{en}}{{cite web|url=http://www.toms.com/evolving-our-giving/l#expanding-local-production|title=TOMS : One for One|publisher=toms.com|accessdate=2014-01-25|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140124085822/http://www.toms.com/evolving-our-giving/l#expanding-local-production|archivedate=2014-01-24}}</ref>

